headline: Examining CrowdStrike’s Valuation After Another 42% Surge and Expanded AI Partnerships in 2025
summary: If you’re watching CrowdStrike Holdings and wondering what your next move should be, you’re not alone. The cybersecurity company’s stock has been on quite a ride, leaving investors buzzing about growth opportunities and asking whether the current price still makes sense. Over the past year, shares have soared 54.2%, with a particularly impressive surge of 42.1% year-to-date.
